# sentence_id = 5
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 1.4
# prose_translation = For just as some people represent many objects by making likenesses with colors and forms (some through art and others through habit) and others again through the voice, so also in the arts mentioned all produce the imitation in rhythm, language, and harmony, whether used separately or mixed.
# literal_translation = For just as also by colors and forms many things imitate some people making-likenesses (the ones indeed through art the others but through habit), others but through the voice, so also in the mentioned arts, all indeed make the imitation in rhythm and language and harmony, by these but either separately or having-been-mixed.
