# sentence_id = 57
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 4.13
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = When Tragedy and Comedy appeared, those who were drawn to either kind of poetry by their natural character became writers of comedies instead of iambics, or producers of tragedies instead of epics, because these forms were greater and more honorable than the others.
# literal_translation = Having-appeared but of the tragedy and comedy the-ones upon either the poetry rushing according to the proper nature the-ones indeed instead of the iambics comic-poets became, the-others but instead of the epics tragedy-teachers, through the greater and more-honorable the forms to-be these than-those.
