# prose_translation = For in composing the Odyssey, he did not include all the things that happened to Odysseus—for example, his being wounded on Parnassus, or his pretending to be mad during the muster, of which events the occurrence of one was not necessary or likely to cause the other; but he constructed the Odyssey around a single action of the kind we speak of, and similarly also the Iliad.
