# sentence_id = 146
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 8.4
# prose_translation = Therefore, just as in other imitative arts a single imitation is an imitation of a single object, so also the plot, since it is an imitation of an action, must be an imitation of a single action and this entire; and the parts of the incidents must be so constructed that if any part is displaced or removed, the whole is disjointed and disturbed.
# literal_translation = It-is-necessary therefore, just-as and in the others imitative-arts the one imitation of-one is, so and the plot, since of-action imitation is, of-one-both to-be and this whole, and the parts to-be-composed of-the incidents so so-as having-been-displaced some part or having-been-taken-away to-differ and to-be-moved the whole;
