# sentence_id = 318
# document_id = 0086-034
# subdoc = 17.14
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = For the story of the Odyssey is not long: a certain person is away from home for many years, is watched by Poseidon, and is alone; and meanwhile the affairs at home are in such a state that his property is being consumed by suitors and his son's life is being plotted against; but he himself arrives, after having been tossed by storm, and having recognized some individuals and made an attack, he himself is saved and destroys his enemies.
# literal_translation = Of-the for Odyssey not long the story is; being-away-from-home some-one years many and being-watched under of-the Poseidon and alone being, still but of-the-things at-home so having-it so-as the money under of-suitors to-be-consumed and the son to-be-plotted-against, himself but he-arrives having-been-stormed, and having-recognized some-ones having-attacked himself indeed was-saved the but enemies he-destroyed.
