# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = Thus those who criticize this kind of language and mock the poet are incorrect—such as Euclid the Elder, who said it was easy to be a poet if one were allowed to lengthen syllables as much as one liked, and he lampooned this style in the line: 'I saw Epichares walking to Marathon,' and 'not... his hellebore.'
