# sentence_id = 444
# subdoc = 23.7
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = Consequently, from both the Iliad and the Odyssey only one or at most two tragedies are produced, whereas from the Cypria many are made, and from the Little Iliad more than eight, such as the Judgment of Arms, Philoctetes, Neoptolemus, Eurypylus, The Begging, The Laconian Women, The Sack of Troy and The Departure, and Sinon and The Trojan Women.
# literal_translation = Consequently from indeed Iliad and Odyssey one tragedy is-made of-each or two only, from but Cypria many and of-the little Iliad more eight, as arms judgment, Philoctetes, Neoptolemus, Eurypylus, begging-expedition, Laconians, of-Troy sack and departure and Sinon and Trojan-women.
