# sentence_id = 452
# subdoc = 24.3
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = Furthermore, it should have excellence of thought and diction. All these were first used by Homer, and used adequately. For each of his poems is constructed on these lines: the Iliad is simple and pathetic, while the Odyssey is complex (for there is recognition throughout) and ethical; moreover, in diction and thought he surpassed all others.
# literal_translation = still the thoughts and the diction to-have well. To-which all Homer has-used and first and sufficiently. And for of-the poems each has-been-composed the indeed Iliad simple and pathetic, the but Odyssey complex (recognition for through-all) and ethical; towards but to-these to-diction and thought all he-surpassed.
