# sentence_id = 455
# subdoc = 24.6
# translation_lang = en
# prose_translation = Epic poetry has a special capacity for extending its scale, because in tragedy it is not possible to represent many parts of the action going on at the same time, but only the part that is on the stage and performed by the actors. In epic, however, because it is a narrative, one can represent many parts being carried out simultaneously, which, if they are appropriate, increase the bulk of the poem.
# literal_translation = Has but towards the to-be-extended the size much certain the epic-poetry proper through the in indeed to-the tragedy not to-be-admitted together being-done many parts to-imitate but the upon of-the stage and of-the actors part only; in but to-the epic-poetry through the narrative to-be it-is many parts together to-make being-carried-out, by of-which proper being increases the of-the poem bulk.
